1.(ditransitive) to give; 2.(with a ou para or an indirect objective pronoun)
; 3.to hand over (to pass something into someone’s hand); 4.to administer (to cause to take (medicine)); 5.(transitive) to give; to issue; to emit; 6.(with the indirect object taking em or an indirect objective pronoun)
; 7.to cause (to produce as a result); 8.to yield; to produce; to generate; 9.(impersonal, transitive, followed by para when transitive) to be possible, to can; 10.(transitive) to throw (to organise an event); 11.(transitive with que; impersonal with em) to report (publish or broadcast news); 12.(transitive with em or with no preposition) to result in; 13.(transitive or auxiliary with para and a verb in the personal infinitive) to suffice, to be enough; 14.(transitive) to make (to tend or be able to become); 15.(ditransitive, with the indirect object taking por or como) to consider (assign some quality to); 16.(transitive with com) to come across (to find something accidentally or in an unexpected condition); 17.(Brazil, vulgar, slang, intransitive, or ditransitive, with the indirect object taking para) to put out, to allow to be sexually penetrated; 18.(Brazil, slang, transitive with de) to defeat by a given score;

1. arm (upper limb); 2. (specifically) upper arm; brachium (part of the arm between the elbow and shoulder); 3. (loosely) any limb or tentacle; 4. arm (part of an object designed to be used with the arm)
; 5. arm; sleeve (part of an item of clothing for the upper body that goes around the arm); 6. arm (part of a furniture for sitting that one can rest one’s arm on); 7. arm (anything that extends out from another thing)
; 8. (music) neck (extended part of a stringed instrument); 9. (geography) arm; inlet (small part of a body of water extending out from the main body); 10. (geography) a smaller range extending from a mountain range; 11. (mechanics) the part of a lever on either side of the fulcrum; 12. (genetics) arm (part of a chromosome extending from the centromere); 13. (astronomy) arm (outer part of a spiral galaxy); 14. arm (person employed to do manual labour); 15. (figuratively) arm; might; power;
